A Cicindela campestris, also known as the green tiger beetle, is a species of beetle that belongs to the family Carabidae. 
It is characterized by its bright green metallic color and elongated, slender body shape. 
The beetle has large, powerful legs that allow it to run quickly on the ground and capture prey in flight. 
Its mandibles are also long and sharp, adapted for piercing and holding prey. 
Cicindela campestris is commonly found in open, sandy habitats like sand dunes, heathlands, and fields. 
They are also active in warm, sunny conditions, particularly during the summer. 
The species is widespread across Europe and parts of Asia, but is considered a threatened species in some regions.
